We also have mono
audio, which mixes

00:11:42.580 --> 00:11:45.250
the right and the left
channels into a single channel,

00:11:45.250 --> 00:11:47.920
and then puts those two
channels into both the earbuds.

00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:51.460
So you can watch videos
with just a single earbud.

00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:55.030
And this also
works in AR and VR.

00:11:55.030 --> 00:11:57.340
We also have magnification,
where you triple tap on

00:11:57.340 --> 00:11:59.170
the screen to zoom in.

00:11:59.170 --> 00:12:01.960
And this works
really well in AR.

00:12:01.960 --> 00:12:04.720
And then we have Switch
Access and TalkBack,

00:12:04.720 --> 00:12:07.750
which I'll get into.

00:12:07.750 --> 00:12:11.260
So designing for accessibility,
things that you can do today?

00:12:11.260 --> 00:12:14.950
Well, Switch Access and
TalkBack requires the app

00:12:14.950 --> 00:12:17.800
to support Android
accessibility APIs.

00:12:17.800 --> 00:12:19.720
This is where you come in.

00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:23.050
The APIs are in Java, so you can
integrate them into your Java

00:12:23.050 --> 00:12:24.780
or C++ apps.

00:12:24.780 --> 00:12:27.460
The switch access makes
it possible for people

00:12:27.460 --> 00:12:29.980
with dexterity impairments
to use your app

00:12:29.980 --> 00:12:32.360
with one or more switches.

00:12:32.360 --> 00:12:34.480
These switches can take
the form of buttons,

00:12:34.480 --> 00:12:37.330
like the volume buttons
on the side of the phone,

00:12:37.330 --> 00:12:38.500
or special sensors.

00:12:38.500 --> 00:12:41.740
Like, Stephen Hawking had
sensors that detected his cheek

00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:43.300
muscle twitches.

00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.299
So with one button,
you can press to cycle

00:12:45.299 --> 00:12:46.840
through the different
items, like you

00:12:46.840 --> 00:12:48.260
see that blue box highlighting.

00:12:48.260 --> 00:12:50.380
And when you get to
the one you want,

00:12:50.380 --> 00:12:53.890
you press the second
button to select it.

00:12:53.890 --> 00:12:56.230
And then we have
TalkBack, which is

00:12:56.230 --> 00:12:58.510
another way you can use to
interact with your phone.

00:12:58.510 --> 00:13:01.470
But I'll let my friend Victor
show you how he uses it

00:13:01.470 --> 00:13:04.758
in a simple tic-tac-toe app.

00:13:04.758 --> 00:13:06.670
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:13:06.670 --> 00:13:08.260
- My name is Victor
Tsaran and I'm

00:13:08.260 --> 00:13:11.320
a technical program manager
on the Android Accessibility

00:13:11.320 --> 00:13:13.120
Services team.

00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:16.310
Among other products,
we work on TalkBack.

00:13:16.310 --> 00:13:18.970
TalkBack is a screen reader
for people who are blind

00:13:18.970 --> 00:13:21.230
or vision impaired.

00:13:21.230 --> 00:13:26.220
The way you use TalkBack is
via special touch gestures.

00:13:26.220 --> 00:13:30.890
The output, the feedback,
is provided by speech.

00:13:30.890 --> 00:13:31.609
- Tic-tac-toe.

00:13:31.609 --> 00:13:33.150
- There are two ways
you can navigate

00:13:33.150 --> 00:13:34.700
the screen with TalkBack.

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:37.400
The first one is called
linear navigation

00:13:37.400 --> 00:13:42.260
and is performed by swiping left
and right with a single finger.

00:13:42.260 --> 00:13:44.720
When the element of
interest is located,

00:13:44.720 --> 00:13:47.081
the user double taps
on it to activate.

00:13:47.081 --> 00:13:48.080
- Next placed in center.

00:13:48.080 --> 00:13:48.990
O's turn.

00:13:48.990 --> 00:13:50.690
O placed in bottom left.

00:13:50.690 --> 00:13:52.230
Empty space button.

00:13:52.230 --> 00:13:53.200
X's turn.

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:53.990
O's turn.

00:13:53.990 --> 00:13:55.100
O placed in bottom right.

00:13:55.100 --> 00:13:57.560
- Another method is
called touch exploration.

00:13:57.560 --> 00:13:59.600
In this method, you
direct the finger

00:13:59.600 --> 00:14:01.640
across the elements
on the screen.

00:14:01.640 --> 00:14:04.130
Once the element of
interest is located,

00:14:04.130 --> 00:14:06.380
you double tap on
it to activate.

00:14:06.380 --> 00:14:07.130
- Column two.

00:14:07.130 --> 00:14:08.180
Empty space button.

00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:09.670
X placed in center left.

00:14:09.670 --> 00:14:12.124
X wins.

00:14:12.124 --> 00:14:13.562
[END PLAYBACK]

